<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  NOW YOU HAVE IT!<br>
Now you know exactly what is being done to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  males</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> in this country (particularly those of european stock, but I won't go into that for concern of evoking the &quot;cover the ears and shout racist&quot; reflex in some.)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Don't gripe and moan about the treatment of women in Afghanistan; it only differs from the treatment of males here in degree, not in kind. (For those of you still studying Dr. Seuss, I said males here are brainwashed and denegrated the same way Ugle claims the Afghan females are, just not as severly... yet.)<br>
<br>
It's okay for us to brainwash and tear down people here according to our commonly accepted bigotries, but don't let the Afghans do it in their own country. Make up your (sexual reference that would otherwise be edited) mind, people. Either females are equal or they are helpless little victims, unable to defend themselves or think for themselves. Such idiotic ideas always imply that insecure males feel the need to put someone down (or insecure &lt;insert target group in power du jour here&gt; for that matter) and therefore found a whipping boy. Which is of course pure bovine leavings. If that were the case, females everywhere would be in the boat the Afghan females are. The only reason the feminazi movement got anywhere in the west was because some men actually *care* about women. <br>
The other fallacy in that is suggesting that it's a matter of brainwashing that puts one person subject to another. Is it brainwashing that children are subject to adults? No? Then why are they subject to the rule of parents and all other adults, if not oppression? Yeah, that thought you're thinking right now as to why... that's why females have historically been subject to males.<br>
<br>
Tell you what; remove all the male soldiers (redundant, I know) guarding the detainees and have only American female members of the military guard them. We can have a lottery on how long it takes before there's a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  successful</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> escape attempt. It'll be measured in hours, not days. Get a clue; the Al Quaida and Taliban forces don't screw around with bovine feces &quot;equality&quot;. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Watch the media, from advertising to movies to video games; repeat that quote again and again, everyone. &quot;. Tell someone they suck long enough and that they only exist to serve and they start believing it. &quot; Ugle has revealed the campaign taking place right here in the U.S.  Five bucks says no one campaigns to put a stop to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> it</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Why does the plight of females in Afghanistan keep coming up? It's totally, completely, and in all other ways <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  irrelevant</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> We are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> fighting in Afghanistan to free the oppressed or enforce political correctness! At least that's not how the campaign was sold to us right after the attack. We are there to eliminate, however possible or necessary, those threats to the U.S. Period. End of public financing. I want to see the balance sheet that indicates that it's cheaper to rebuild Afghanistan than eliminate its population. I want to see the reports indicating that rebuilding Afghanistan (yet again) will eliminate the threat of harm to the U.S. <br>
I think the Afghans are idiots for slapping their foreheads against the floor 6 times a day; in other words, for following Islam. Is that a reason to &quot;liberate&quot; Afghanistan? So why do some people think their disapproval of the other practices of the Afghans (like severe penalties for violating strict religious rules relating to Islam) is reason to &quot;liberate&quot; Afghanistan?<br>
<br>
Maybe we'll get lucky and history will repeat in more ways than our following in British and Russian footsteps. Maybe there will be the Afghan equivalent of &quot;boat people&quot; flooding the U.S. as happened after the Indochinese War. Bringing with them, as did the boat people, their cultural philosophies.<br>
Soldiers will bring home war brides.. excuse me.. war hubbies.<br>
<br>
I know, I know.. I'm dreaming. A rotting republic, once its turned to empire, can't be saved. But I can't help hoping.<br>
