Carter was that creepy teacher you always prayed you wouldn't get in highschool; the one more concerned about the social climate of his classroom than in teaching. <br>
The Iranians coughed up the hostages after Reagan had won the election. The fact that he convinced them along with the rest of the world that the days of a balless wonder in the White House were over is often dismissed.<br>
As someone whose life was destroyed by Jimmy Carter, and who was rebuilt by President Reagan, I can verify the truth of what Ugle said in another thread: tell someone they're no good, and they won't be. Tell them they can't, and they won't.<br>
 <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Long before 9/11, President Reagan was calling the common man, the firefighters, the police, the mail carriers, the guy who makes the donuts, heroes.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
 Carter told us we were impotant and unimportant. That the future was going to be terrible because we were bad and there's nothing we can do about it. <br>
